channels.label: Start Frames
channels.description: Counter tracking the number of SOF bytes received

channels.label: Frames Acknowledged
channels.description: Counter tracking the number of frames acknowledged by the controller

channels.label: Frames Rejected
channels.description: Counter tracking the number of frames rejected by the controller

channels.label: Frames Cancelled
channels.description: Counter tracking the number of frames cancelled by the controller

channels.label: OOF Bytes Received
channels.description: Counter tracking the number of out of flow bytes received

channels.label: Received Checksum Errors
channels.description: Counter tracking the number of frames received with checksum errors

channels.label: Binary Sensor
channels.description: Indicates if a sensor has triggered

channels.label: Sensor (seismic intensity)
channels.description: Indicates the current seismic intensity level

channels.label: Motion Alarm
channels.description: Indicates if a motion alarm is triggered

channels.label: Tamper Alarm
channels.description: Indicates if the tamper alarm is triggered

channels.label: Alarm (general)
channels.description: Indicates if an alarm is triggered

value.label: Z-Wave Node 004: HS2SK-Z Smart Metering Plug

channels.label: Switch
channels.description: Switch the power on and off

channels.label: Start HLS Stream
channels.description: Lower the delay to start casting the camera by creating the files non stop in case they are needed.

channels.label: Poll Image
channels.description: This can be used to trigger snapshot updates when an external PIR, button or other form of sensor turns this channel ON.

channels.label: Image
channels.description: Low frame rate image from your camera. Recommend this is NOT used unless you have large pollTime.

channels.label: GIF Recording
channels.description: Indicates how long the recording will occur for and when the file is created, the channel will change to 0 by itself.

channels.label: GIF History
channels.description: A history of the last GIFs created in a CSV formatted string.

channels.label: GIF History Length
channels.description: How many GIFs are stored in the history.

channels.label: MP4 Recording
channels.description: Indicates how long the recording will occur for and when the file is created, the channel will change to 0 by itself.

channels.label: MP4 History
channels.description: A history of the last mp4 recordings created in a CSV formatted string.

channels.label: MP4 History Length
channels.description: How many mp4 recordings are stored in the history.

channels.label: Last Motion Type
channels.description: A string that contains the type of motion alarm that was last triggered.

channels.label: Control FFmpeg Motion Alarm
channels.description: Enable/Disable the motion alarm and control the sensitivity.

channels.label: Enable Motion Alarm
channels.description: By using this feature you can stop the camera from sending e-mails when you are actually home.

channels.label: External Motion
channels.description: Use any external sensor like a ZWave PIR sensor to flag that the camera has motion in its field of view.

channels.label: Enable Audio Alarm
channels.description: By using this feature you can stop the camera from sending e-mails when you are having a party.

channels.label: Audio Alarm Threshold
channels.description: By moving this control you should be able to change how sensitive the audio alarm is to soft or loud noises.

channels.label: Auto LED
channels.description: Turn the automatic mode for the LED ON and OFF.

channels.label: LED Controls
channels.description: Turn the LED ON and OFF and if supported also 0-100% dimming.

channels.label: Pan
channels.description: Pan the camera to a new position.

channels.label: Tilt
channels.description: Tilt the camera to a new position.

channels.label: Zoom
channels.description: Zoom the camera to a new value.

channels.label: Go To Preset
channels.description: Move a P.T.Z camera to this ONVIF preset location.

channels.label: MJPEG URL
channels.description: A link you can use in openHAB/HABpanel to fetch a MJPEG video feed from the camera.

channels.label: RTSP URL
channels.description: A link that the camera uses for RTSP.

channels.label: Image URL
channels.description: A link you can use to fetch a static image from the camera.

channels.label: HLS URL
channels.description: A link you can use in openHAB to cast video feeds.

channels.label: Enable Privacy Mode
channels.description: Turn the Privacy Mode on and off.
